You are not designing a new brand.

You are producing final individual image assets for an existing brand system.

The brand is:

Oakwood Learning Hub

Tagline:
Supporting families, empowering students, advancing education.

The MASTER LOGO is locked.
Do not change the logo.
Do not redesign the tree.
Do not change the brand direction.
Do not create a new style.
Do not simplify the style.
Do not replace the visual language with generic icons.

Use the attached reference images as the visual source of truth:

1. Oakwood master logo
2. Oakwood logo system / brand guide
3. Oakwood brand icon system
4. Previously approved single character illustration: student girl with eyes, mouth, nose, botanical branches and root/hub detail

The goal is to recreate every requested icon as a separate, high-quality, standalone image file in the same visual language as the approved references.

IMPORTANT:
Do not create one combined sheet.
Do not create a contact sheet.
Do not place multiple icons in one image.
Do not crop from the previous sheet.
Do not make low-detail placeholders.
Do not make faceless characters.
Do not remove facial features.
Do not put leaves or branches in front of the face.
Do not let botanical elements cover the eyes, nose, mouth, or important body details.
Do not use generic flat icons.
Do not use childish cartoon style.
Do not use realistic illustration style.
Do not use 3D, gradients, shadows, glossy effects, badges, shields, crests, or corporate tech/circuit-board style.
Do not output SVG unless explicitly asked later.
Output each item as its own separate PNG image.

Style requirements for every generated icon:
- Calm, premium, family-friendly, UK education brand feeling
- Organic flowing linework
- Soft botanical accents
- Oakwood palette only:
  - soft green #769a7c
  - dark green #4a5d4d
  - sage #a8bfa6
  - warm beige #d8cbb2
