- Include subtle root/hub/network detail below the character where appropriate, but do not make it busy
- The character should feel like part of the Oakwood Learning Hub system, not a generic avatar

Generate the following assets as separate files:

ROLE ICONS

1. parent-neutral.png
Description:
A gender-neutral parent icon. Adult figure, calm expression, friendly face with eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth. Hair and clothing should be neutral, not strongly male or female. Botanical branches behind the shoulders. Subtle root/hub linework below. Must feel supportive, safe, parent-like and premium.

2. parent-female.png
Description:
Female parent icon. Adult woman, warm calm expression, eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth visible. Elegant organic hair linework. Botanical branches behind the shoulders. Leaves must not cover the face. Subtle root/hub linework below. Must feel caring, intelligent, and trustworthy.

3. parent-male.png
Description:
Male parent icon. Adult man, warm calm expression, eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth visible. Refined hair and optional very subtle beard/stubble if it fits the style. Botanical branches behind the shoulders. Leaves must not cover the face. Subtle root/hub linework below. Must feel supportive, reliable, and modern.

4. student-primary-girl.png
Description:
Younger school-age girl, roughly UK primary school age. Warm expression, eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth visible. Hair can be pigtails, braid, or soft shoulder-length style, but must remain elegant and not cartoonish. School-friendly clothing. Botanical accents behind the shoulders. Leaves must not cover the face. Subtle root/hub detail below.

5. student-primary-boy.png
Description:
Younger school-age boy, roughly UK primary school age. Warm expression, eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth visible. Hair should be simple and natural. School-friendly clothing, not sporty or childish. Botanical accents behind the shoulders. Leaves must not cover the face. Subtle root/hub detail below.

6. student-secondary-girl.png
Description:
Older student girl, roughly year 7 and above. More mature school-age look than primary girl. Warm expression, eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth visible. School jumper/shirt or refined school-style clothing may be used. Botanical accents behind. Subtle root/hub detail below. Must feel capable, calm, and education-focused.

7. student-secondary-boy.png
Description:
Older student boy, roughly year 7 and above. More mature school-age look than primary boy. Warm expression, eyes, eyebrows, nose and mouth visible. School jumper/hoodie or refined school-style clothing may be used, but keep it premium and calm. Botanical accents behind. Subtle root/hub detail below.

CORE APP ICONS

8. family-hub-icon.png
Description:
Family hub icon. A small family/group under or beside an abstract Oakwood tree/hub structure. Should communicate family connection, central learning hub, support, and shared progress. Use organic linework, not corporate network graphics. No text.

9. lessons-icon.png
Description:
Lessons icon. Open book with subtle oak branches or learning-growth lines emerging from it. Calm, educational, premium. No text. Avoid childish school clipart.

10. quiz-icon.png
Description:
Quiz/test icon. A question mark or assessment card combined with a subtle leaf or check detail. Must look like assessment/quiz, not help/support. No text.

11. homework-icon.png
Description:
Homework icon. Checklist or assignment sheet with soft leaf detail. Should clearly communicate tasks/homework. No text.

12. report-icon.png
Description:
Reports/progress icon. Calm chart/progress bars combined with botanical growth element. Should feel analytical but warm. No harsh corporate chart style. No text.

13. ai-icon.png
Description:
AI assistant icon. Soft speech bubble or spark detail combined with a leaf/branch motif. Must feel intelligent and supportive, not robotic or sci-fi. No robot head. No circuit-board style. No text.

14. resources-icon.png
Description:
Resources icon. Folder, document stack, or library/resource symbol with subtle botanical detail. Should communicate saved learning materials, PDFs, links, sources. No text.

15. messages-icon.png
Description:
Messages/communication icon. Speech bubbles with subtle node/leaf/hub detail. Should feel like parent-student-teacher communication. No text.

16. settings-icon.png
Description:
Settings icon. Gear with a subtle leaf or Oakwood motif inside. Calm and premium, not industrial. No text.

17. pin-icon.png
Description:
PIN/security icon. Lock or PIN pad with subtle Oakwood leaf detail. Should communicate local privacy and security. No text.

BACKGROUND ASSETS

18. family-hub-background.png
Description:
Wide web app background for family/parent hub pages. Soft neutral #fdfbf7 background. Very subtle botanical branches, Oakwood tree/root motifs, and warm green/beige accents. Must not compete with UI cards. Leave lots of clean negative space. No text. No people. No busy pattern. Suitable for login, profile selection, parent dashboard, family hub.

19. student-learning-background.png
Description:
Wide web app background for student learning pages. Soft neutral #fdfbf7 background. Subtle learning motifs: branches, roots, books, gentle progress lines, small node/path accents. Must remain calm and not busy. No text. No people. Suitable for lessons, homework, quiz, reports, student dashboard.

LOGO ASSETS

20. master-logo.png
Use the attached master logo exactly.
Do not redraw it.
Do not alter it.
Do not change the text, tree, tagline, colours, or proportions.

21. compact-logo-horizontal.png
Create a compact horizontal logo based strictly on the attached Oakwood logo system. It should use the same tree mark and text “Oakwood Learning Hub”. No tagline. Do not redesign. Do not change typography personality.

22. compact-logo-stacked.png
Create a compact stacked logo based strictly on the attached Oakwood logo system. Tree mark above, “Oakwood Learning Hub” below. No tagline. Do not redesign.

23. app-icon.png
Create app icon version based strictly on the attached Oakwood logo system. Tree symbol only, no text, no tagline. Must work in square app icon usage. Keep the same Oakwood tree style.

24. micro-icon.png
Create micro icon version based strictly on the attached Oakwood logo system. Extremely simplified tree mark for favicon/tiny UI. No text. Must remain recognisable at small size.

Output requirements:
- Produce each image as an individual PNG file.
- File names must match exactly the names listed above.
- Do not combine them into a single sheet.
- Do not add labels.
- Do not add captions.
- Do not add numbers.
